{{!--
  Maintainer notes (not emitted in G-code):
  - 4-axis Mach3 post for generic CNC routers/mills with A-axis rotary table.
  - A axis is the rotary axis (rotation around X by default).
  - Mach3 supports M6 tool change — included in the header before spindle start.
  - Lines starting with ";" are operator-visible comments in output.
  - Template context keys: resources/posts/README.md (PostContext / renderPost).
  - Additional context for 4-axis: axisCount, aAxisRangeDeg, aAxisOrientation.
  - % tape start/end markers are Mach3 convention (RS-274 standard).
--}}
%
; {{machine.name}} — {{machine.id}}
; 4-AXIS (A-ROTARY) G-CODE — mach3_4axis dialect
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; UNVERIFIED G-CODE — verify every line against your Mach3 configuration
; and your rotary attachment manual before running on the machine.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; CRITICAL 4TH AXIS CHECKS BEFORE RUNNING:
; (1) Confirm the rotary attachment is firmly clamped to the table and the
;     A-axis motor/driver is enabled in Mach3 Config > Motor Tuning.
; (2) Confirm the workpiece is centred on the rotary chuck — off-centre
;     stock causes gouging and crashes.
; (3) Confirm cylinder diameter matches the value used to generate toolpaths.
; (4) Set A-axis WCS zero (usually the left face of the cylinder, A=0).
;     Use Mach3 DRO to zero the A axis at your reference position.
; (5) Air-cut with spindle off at 10% feed override before a real cut.
; (6) Confirm your Mach3 configuration supports the A word (Config > General
;     Config > Rotary axis enabled). Verify steps/degree in Motor Tuning.
; (7) Confirm soft limits for A axis match your rotary table travel.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Retract order: lift Z to a safe radial clearance before commanding large A moves
; (toolpath lines already use clearance Z between passes; header retract is machine max Z).
; Before production: dry run — spindle off, Z high, feed reduced.
; Compare a short program to a known-good file from your CAM package.
; See docs/MACHINES.md — safe Z, WCS, units, spindle M-codes.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Work area (mm): {{machine.workAreaMm.x}} x {{machine.workAreaMm.y}} x {{machine.workAreaMm.z}}
{{#if machine.aAxisRangeDeg}}; A-axis range: +/-{{machine.aAxisRangeDeg}} deg (verify against Mach3 soft limits)
{{/if}}
; --- Safety header ---
G21              ; millimeters — must match Mach3 setup (Config > Native Units)
G90              ; absolute distance mode (X Y Z A all absolute)
G17              ; XY plane for G2/G3 arcs; switch to G18 (XZ) if needed for 4-axis arcs
G40              ; cancel cutter radius compensation
G80              ; cancel canned cycles
{{#if wcsLine}}; Active work offset — verify fixture zero matches G54-G59 selection
{{wcsLine}}
{{/if}}
{{#if operationLabel}}; Operation: {{operationLabel}}
{{/if}}
; --- Tool call (Mach3 supports M6 tool change) ---
; Verify tool number, length offset, and diameter in Mach3 tool table.
T{{#if toolNumber}}{{toolNumber}}{{else}}1{{/if}} M6            ; select tool {{#if toolNumber}}{{toolNumber}}{{else}}1{{/if}} and execute tool change
; Home / safe position — retract Z before rotating A to avoid collisions
G0 Z{{machine.workAreaMm.z}} ; safe Z retract — adjust to your actual safe clearance
; Spindle on (Mach3 — confirm S value and M3/M4 match your spindle setup)
{{spindleOn}}
{{#if inverseTimeFeed}}; --- Inverse-time feed mode (G93) for continuous rotary axis motion ---
; F-word = 1/time (inverse minutes). Each G1 block must carry its own F value.
; G94 is restored after the toolpath to return to normal feed-per-minute mode.
G93              ; inverse-time feed mode ON
{{/if}}; --- 4-axis toolpath moves begin (X Y Z A words) ---
{{#each toolpathLines}}
{{this}}
{{/each}}
; --- end toolpath ---
{{#if inverseTimeFeed}}G94              ; restore feed-per-minute mode
{{/if}}; Spindle off
{{spindleOff}}
; Retract Z to machine max clearance before parking
; (Toolpath already returns A to 0 deg and retracts Z to clearance;
;  this final retract ensures the tool is at machine-max Z for unload.)
G0 Z{{machine.workAreaMm.z}} ; full retract for unload
G0 X0 Y0         ; park X Y — adjust to your preferred home position
M30              ; program end — rewinds Mach3 to start
%
